quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,88,"Do not extend your eyes toward that by which We have given enjoyment to [certain] categories of them [i.e., the disbelievers], and do not grieve over them. And lower your wing [i.e., show kindness] to the believers."
  15,89,"And say, "
  15,90,"Just as We had revealed [scriptures] to the separators{1}",footnotes:1:Those who separated from the teachings of their prophets.  Another meaning is "As We sent down [punishment] on the sworn opponents [to Allāh's message]."
  16,67,"And from the fruits of the palm trees and grapevines you take intoxicant and good provision.{1} Indeed in that is a sign for a people who reason.",footnotes:1:This verse was revealed before the prohibition of intoxicants.  It alludes to the fact that there are both evil and good possibilities in certain things.
  16,68,"And your Lord inspired to the bee, "
  16,69,"Then eat from all the fruits{1} and follow the ways of your Lord laid down [for you].",footnotes:1:i.e., delicious substances found by the bee.
  17,34,"And do not approach the property of an orphan, except in the way that is best,{1} until he reaches maturity. And fulfill [every] commitment. Indeed, the commitment is ever [that about which one will be] questioned.",footnotes:1:i.e., to improve or increase it.
  17,35,"And give full measure when you measure, and weigh with an even [i.e., honest] balance. That is the best [way] and best in result."
  17,36,"And do not pursue{1} that of which you have no knowledge. Indeed, the hearing, the sight and the heart - about all those [one] will be questioned.",footnotes:1:i.e., do not assume and do not say.
  18,1,"[All] praise is [due] to Allāh, who has sent down upon His Servant [Muḥammad (ﷺ)] the Book and has not made therein any deviance.{1}",footnotes:1:From the truth or the straight path.
  18,2,"[He has made it] straight, to warn of severe punishment from Him and to give good tidings to the believers who do righteous deeds that they will have a good reward [i.e., Paradise]."
  18,3,"In which they will remain forever"